## Math Notation

| Formula | Meaning | Elixir | Nx |
|---------|---------|--------|----|
| `cos(πr)` | Cosine decay curve | `:math.cos(:math.pi() * ratio)` | (computed in Elixir) |
| `‖g‖₂` | L2 norm of gradient vector | `:math.sqrt(Enum.sum(g, &(&1*&1)))` | `Nx.sqrt(Nx.sum(Nx.multiply(g, g)))` |
| `g · (c/‖g‖)` | Scale gradient to max norm c | `Enum.map(g, &(&1 * scale))` | `Nx.multiply(g, scale)` |

<details>
<summary>All symbols so far (notebooks 00-10)</summary>

| Symbol | Meaning |
|--------|---------|
| `Σᵢ xᵢ`, `xᵢ`, `n` | Sum, indexing, count |
| `W ∈ ℝ^{V×d}`, `W[i]` | Matrix shape, row lookup |
| `μ, σ², ε` | Mean, variance, epsilon |
| `γ, β` | Learnable scale and shift |
| `Q, K, V`, `d_k` | Attention projections, head dim |
| `softmax`, `^T` | Probabilities, transpose |
| `GELU`, `Φ`, `erf` | Activation, Gaussian CDF, error function |
| `x_{l+1} = x_l + F(x_l)` | Residual connection |
| `W_E^T` | Weight-tied output projection |
| `L`, `log`, `P(y\|x)` | Loss, logarithm, conditional probability |
| `α`, `β₁/β₂` | Learning rate, decay rates |
| `∇`, `θ`, `λ` | Gradient, parameters, weight decay |
| `‖g‖₂` | L2 (global) norm |

</details>

## Key Concepts

| Concept | What it means |
|---------|--------------|
| **Learning rate schedule** | Changes LR over time: linear warmup → cosine decay → constant minimum |
| **Warmup** | Start with tiny LR and ramp up to prevent destructive early updates |
| **Cosine decay** | Smoothly decrease LR following a cosine curve |
| **Gradient clipping** | Scales all gradients down if their global norm exceeds a threshold |
| **Weight decay groups** | Only decay 2D+ tensors (weights); skip biases and layer norm parameters |
